<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/421</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-14T16:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8244. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 671. Embassy’s 10431, June 5, 11 a.m., your 721.<note n="1" xml:id="d353fn1">Not printed.</note> Until the permanent Swedish
                                agreement is ratified by the Swedish Government we must, of course,
                                continue to operate under the <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi>
                                and will continue to allow vessels to leave the United States
                                whenever compensation ships from Sweden are named and sail for this
                                side. We are now working on matter of <hi rend="italic">Sydic</hi>
                                and other boats available for South America.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>